If people think Bryan Johnson and his son are eccentric, at one point Dr. Alexis Carrel saved the life of a friend's newborn daughter who was bleeding and highly anemic by connecting her blood circulation to that of her father, literally joining them into one organism. It worked.

Artery from father's wrist, an anastomosis with a vein on the newborn daughter's knee. She was pale and unconscious, close to death, immediately flushed red and started recovering in seconds. Medical Record 73(22):885-887, May 30, 1908.
